  "text": "We use the SGD algorithm with the Nesterov momentum to train all the models for 400 epochs on CIFAR-10/CIFAR-100 and 40 epochs on SVHN, both with a total mini-batch size 64 on two GPUs. The learning rate starts with 0.1 and is reduced by a factor 10 at the 1/2, 3/4 and 7/8 fractions of the number of training epochs. Similar to [CITATION_1] 10] , the weight decay is 0.0001, the momentum is 0.9, and the weights are initialized as in [CITATION_2] . We follow ResNets to design our networks: use three groups of fusion units with the number of filter channels being 16, 32, 64, respectively, and use a Conv-BN-ReLU as a basic layer with the filter size of 3 × 3. In the merge-and-run fusion, merge (+ in Figure 6(b) ) is an averaging operation. All the other + op- erations in Figures 6 are between BN and ReLU. Our implementation is based on MXNet [CITATION_3] , and the code is available at https://github.com/zlmzju/fusenet.",
